In terms of product type segmentation, bonded abrasives continue to dominate the market due to their versatility and applicability in various industrial processes such as grinding, cutting, and sharpening. The demand for coated abrasives is also on the rise, particularly in applications requiring polishing and surface finishing. Superabrasives, characterized by their exceptional hardness and durability, cater to specialized industries where high-performance abrasives are essential for precision machining and cutting operations. Market players have been investing in research and development to enhance the performance and durability of superabrasives, thus expanding their applications across different industries.

